 xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 21, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ivr1665702776431.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ivr1665702776431.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ivr1665702776431.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ivr1665702776431\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      SQL Editor\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"ivr1665702776431__sql_editor_31823\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Use the SQL Editor to send ad hoc queries to the database. This is only supported by databases that include a Data Manipulation Language (DML).\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ivr1665702776431__p_d8630e1_d8631e1_d8632e1\">To open this tool, choose Main Menu ( ≡ ) &gt;\n            <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Edit SQL</span>. </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ivr1665702776431__p_d8636e1_d8637e1_d8638e1\">You can connect to databases that support SQL, and to some others to a limited extent. For more information on the extent of support, see the DBMS connector documentation for your DBMS.</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"ivr1665702776431__fig_d8639e1_d8640e1_d8641e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>SQL Workbench</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"SQL Workbench\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/sqleditor.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ivr1665702776431__topic_d6582e1_d6583e1_d6584e1_d6585e1_d6586e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d110325e76\">\n                  \n Fields\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ivr1665702776431__li_d4016e1_d4017e1_d4018e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Data Path</span>—DBMS or network path used to access the data. If you enter an incorrect path assignment on this form, an implicit and immediate <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">apexit</span> is generated; that is, you exit the application immediately.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ivr1665702776431__li_d4019e1_d4020e1_d4021e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">SQL Command</span>—SQL command to execute. Do not use a semicolon when entering the command. SQL statements that exceed 2 kilobytes are truncated.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ivr1665702776431__li_d4022e1_d4023e1_d4024e1\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">DBMS Output</span>—query results.\n </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ivr1665702776431__topic_d6587e1_d6588e1_d6589e1_d6590e1_d6591e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d110325e107\">\n                  \n How to\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ivr1665702776431__p_d8651e1_d8652e1_d8653e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"eta1665702776509.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eta1665702776509.html\" title=\"You can use the SQL Editor to query a database using ad hoc SQL queries.\">Querying a Database</a>\n</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ffw1719409087502.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>SQL and Stored Procedures Support</a><p>For SQL-enabled databases, you can use the sql ProcScript instruction and SQL Editor to send SQL instructions to the database. Some databases also support stored procedures.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528729\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528729\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "SQL Editor Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 21, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 SQL Editor Use the SQL Editor to send ad hoc queries to the database. This is only supported by databases that include a Data Manipulation Language (DML). To open this tool, choose Main Menu ( ≡ ) > Edit SQL . You can connect to databases that support SQL, and to some others to a limited extent. For more information on the extent of support, see the DBMS connector documentation for your DBMS. Figure 1. SQL Workbench Fields Data Path —DBMS or network path used to access the data. If you enter an incorrect path assignment on this form, an implicit and immediate apexit is generated; that is, you exit the application immediately. SQL Command —SQL command to execute. Do not use a semicolon when entering the command. SQL statements that exceed 2 kilobytes are truncated. DBMS Output —query results. How to Querying a Database Related Links SQL and Stored Procedures Support For SQL-enabled databases, you can use the sql ProcScript instruction and SQL Editor to send SQL instructions to the database. Some databases also support stored procedures. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}